%N A396970 Square array A(n,k), n >= 1, k >= 0, read by antidiagonals downwards, where column k is the expansion of e.g.f. B^k(x), where B(x) is the e.g.f. of A001028.
%H A396970 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A396970/b396970.txt">Antidiagonals n = 1..140, flattened</a>
%F A396970 E.g.f. B(x) satisfies B'(x) = 1 + B^l(x), where B^l(x) denotes the l-th iterate of B, with B(0) = 0.
%F A396970 Let a(n,k,l) = n! * [x^n] B^k(x), where B^k(x) is the k-th iterate of B.
%F A396970 a(n,0,l) = 0^(n-1) and a(n,k,l) = a(n,k-1,l) + Sum_{j=1..n-1} binomial(n-1,j) * a(j,k+l-1,l) * a(n-j,k-1,l) for k > 0.
%F A396970 A(n,k) = a(n,k,2).
%e A396970 Square array begins:
%e A396970   1,   1,    1,     1,     1,      1,      1, ...
%e A396970   0,   1,    2,     3,     4,      5,      6, ...
%e A396970   0,   2,    7,    15,    26,     40,     57, ...
%e A396970   0,   7,   37,   108,   238,    445,    747, ...
%e A396970   0,  37,  269,  1031,  2838,   6385,  12547, ...
%e A396970   0, 269, 2535, 12398, 42013, 112790, 258094, ...
%e A396970   ...
%Y A396970 Columns k=0..2 give A063524, A001028, A001028(n+1).
